FT  07 DEC 94 / UK Company News: Morris Ashby rises 30%
A 30 per cent increase in interim pre-tax profits, from Pounds 839,000 to
Pounds 1.09m, was reported by Morris Ashby, the USM-quoted diecasting and
machining group.
The outcome for the half-year to September 30 was achieved on turnover up by
Pounds 2.32m to Pounds 13.9m, with the bulk of the increase coming from the
motor car, commercial vehicle and machine tool sectors, according to Mr
Norman Gardner, chairman.
The domestic appliance sector had been the only significant downturn, he
added.
Earnings came out at 6.7p (6.3p) per share, and the interim dividend is
raised to 2.2p (2p).
